net.bytebuddy.dynamic.scaffold

Class TypeExtensionDelegate

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.bytebuddy.dynamic.scaffold.TypeExtensionDelegate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TypeWriter.FieldPool, TypeWriter.MethodPool, Instrumentation.Context, Instrumentation.Context.ExtractableView, AuxiliaryType.MethodAccessorFactory

    public class TypeExtensionDelegate
extends Object
implements Instrumentation.Context.ExtractableView, AuxiliaryType.MethodAccessorFactory, TypeWriter.MethodPool, TypeWriter.FieldPool
    This delegate offers a default implementation of an instrumentation context and a method accessor factory. For convenience, all extension information is stored in a format that allows using this class as a method pool for defining any accessor methods on the accessed type. Note that this delegate represents a mutable structure where registrations cannot be revoked.

      • getRegisteredAccessors

        public Iterable<MethodDescription> getRegisteredAccessors()

        Returns:

      • cache

        public FieldDescription cache(StackManipulation fieldValue,
                              TypeDescription fieldType)
        Description copied from interface: Instrumentation.Context
        Caches a single value by storing it in form of a private, final and static field. By caching values, expensive instance creations can be avoided and object identity can be preserved. The field is initiated in a generated class's static initializer.
        Specified by:
        cache in interface Instrumentation.Context
        Parameters:
        fieldValue - A stack manipulation for creating the value that is to be cached in a static field. After executing the stack manipulation, exactly one value must be put onto the operand stack which is assignable to the given fieldType.
        fieldType - The type of the field for storing the cached value. This field's type determines the value that is put onto the operand stack by this method's returned stack manipulation.
        Returns:
        A description of a field that was defined on the instrumented type which contains the given value.

      • wrapForTypeInitializerInterception

        public TypeWriter.MethodPool wrapForTypeInitializerInterception(TypeWriter.MethodPool methodPool)
        Wraps the given method pool in order to prepend any initializations of field caches. At the same time, invoking this method disables the field cache for further use as it is not possible to define further cached values from a type initializer once this initializer is written.
        Parameters:
        methodPool - The method pool that contains user interceptions which needs to be wrapped.
        Returns:
        A method pool that represents this user method pool but is capable of defining field caches.
